  <Properties>
    <Name>JFD's Civilizations - Great Mongolia (Bogd Gegeen)</Name>
    <Teaser>Adds [COLOR_CYAN]Great Mongolia under Bogd Gegeen[ENDCOLOR]. Click for details.</Teaser>
    <Description>MONGOLIA (BOGD KHAN)[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]UNIQUE TRAIT: ELEVATED BY THE MANY[NEWLINE]When a Great Prophet is spawend, Barbarian Units on the same landmass are converted to your control. Cities with a Great Prophet stationed in them convert [ICON_PEACE] Faith Per Turn to cultural border expansion.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]UNIQUE UNIT: MANLAIBAATAR (GREAT GENERAL)[NEWLINE]The Manlaibaatar is the unique Great General replacement for Great Mongolia. The standard [ICON_STRENGTH] Combat Strength bonus conferred by a Great General to nearby friendly Units is doubled within friendly borders. In addition, bonus points toward a Manlaibaatar are generated for every Barbarian Unit that converts to your ownership when a Great Prophet is spawned.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]UNIQUE BUILDING: GATE OF PEACE AND HAPPINESS (TEMPLE)[NEWLINE]The unique Gate of Peace and Happiness replaces the Temple for Great Mongolia. Unlike the Temple, this building does not provide any intrinsic [ICON_PEACE] Faith. Instead, it yields [ICON_PEACE] Faith based on the city's [ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Local Happiness. It does not require any maintenance. Ensure your cities are content to maximize the Gate's faith output.</Description>
    <Authors>JFD, DMS, Agla, Sukritact, JakeWalrusWhale</Authors>
